# Forecast: version must appear in commit messages

When a commit changes **any** of the following, the **commit message must explicitly state the new Forecast app version** (e.g. `v1.9.0` in the subject or first line of the body):

- [`forecast/service-worker.js`](forecast/service-worker.js) — `VERSION` constant (and derived cache names)
- [`forecast/manifest.json`](forecast/manifest.json) — `version` field
- [`forecast/index.html`](forecast/index.html) — `?v=` cache-bust query strings on CSS/JS assets

**Examples (good):**

- `forecast: Enable Radar; release v1.9.0`
- `forecast v1.9.0: radar section, offline cache, README`

**Avoid:** bumping those files while the message only describes features with no version string.

Prefer keeping all three locations in sync (e.g. `forecast/version.ps1` from repo docs) and reflecting that single version in the commit message.
